constexpr auto cend();

{{dcl | num=2 | since=c++23 |
constexpr auto cend() const requires ranges::range&lt;const D&gt;;

The default implementation of {{tt|cend()}} member function returns the sentinel for the constant iterator of the range.

{{image|range-begin-end.svg}}

@1@ Let {{c|derived}} be a reference bound to {{c|static_cast&lt;D&amp;&gt;(*this)}}. Equivalent to {{c|return ranges::cend(derived);}}.

@2@ Same as {{v|1}}, except that {{c|derived}} is {{c|static_cast&lt;const D&amp;&gt;(*this)}}.

===Parameters===
(none)

===Return value===
The sentinel for the constant iterator of the range.

===Notes===
All range adaptors and range factories in the standard library and {{lc|std::ranges::subrange}} use the default implementation of {{tt|cend}}.
